WEBVTT

00:46.666 --> 00:49.708
'My bright soul...My beloved father
Dedicate this film to you - Your Pradeep'

03:29.125 --> 03:31.333
Dr Pinto! So how's it going?

03:32.208 --> 03:34.750
Hello Mr Murphy. Come, sit.

03:36.750 --> 03:39.416
I have a bad news.
I don't think this radio will work.

03:39.458 --> 03:41.416
- What?
- All components are wet.

03:42.041 --> 03:44.625
I've spent the last three days
trying to figure it out.

03:44.708 --> 03:49.041
If I had a time machine, I'd have
prevented this radio from getting wet.

03:49.125 --> 03:51.833
So you're thinking about
time travel now, huh!

03:51.875 --> 03:53.416
What choice do I have!

03:53.458 --> 03:56.083
You're adamant about
wanting only this radio.

03:56.333 --> 03:58.250
And I don't want to disappoint you.

03:58.416 --> 04:00.166
I know you want to
give this to your father.

04:00.208 --> 04:03.166
But there are so many radios here.
Why don't you choose any of these?

04:03.250 --> 04:05.958
No...No, Doctor Pinto,
this radio is very special to him

04:06.000 --> 04:08.083
Actually, dad had bought
this with his first salary.

04:08.125 --> 04:09.166
Can you imagine?

04:09.208 --> 04:11.375
Doctor, I know you're the only
person who can fix this!

04:11.416 --> 04:12.500
Please!!

04:13.083 --> 04:15.125
So I must invent a time machine now!

04:15.208 --> 04:17.125
Sir, I didn't mean that, sir.
Come on!

04:18.708 --> 04:20.500
'Anyways, sir...'

04:20.875 --> 04:23.250
'Despite knowing it's fictitious,
I'm asking you this.'

04:23.291 --> 04:25.166
'Time machine and time travel'

04:25.208 --> 04:26.791
'What do you think about it?'

04:27.125 --> 04:30.583
Come on, Mr Murphy. Is there
anything you don't know?

04:30.875 --> 04:31.875
Einstein.

04:32.083 --> 04:35.125
Einstein himself says
that time is an illusion.

04:35.625 --> 04:39.708
I mean the past, present
and future, this won't change.

04:39.958 --> 04:43.416
They exactly play out
as they are designed to be.

04:43.833 --> 04:45.083
Like Krishna says,

04:45.125 --> 04:46.333
in the Bhagavad Gita,

04:46.500 --> 04:48.291
Kalaya Tasmai Namaha.

04:48.500 --> 04:50.541
We have to dance to the whims of time.

04:50.708 --> 04:52.083
For example, this radio.

04:52.125 --> 04:54.000
I think it's done and dusted.

04:54.041 --> 04:55.083
I tried my best.

04:55.125 --> 04:57.000
I don't think this
will work any more.

04:57.041 --> 04:58.875
Its old components are tough to get

04:59.000 --> 05:00.375
I have lost all hopes.

05:00.458 --> 05:02.666
Perhaps, you also can try fixing it?

05:09.958 --> 05:11.000
Sir

05:12.666 --> 05:14.500
Sir, it's working...

05:16.958 --> 05:19.541
Didn't you say the components are wet?

05:19.625 --> 05:21.291
How is this possible, sir?

05:22.375 --> 05:24.833
This is impossible!

05:25.791 --> 05:29.875
Sir, are the mic and transmitters
in the radio emitting this noise?

05:29.958 --> 05:33.083
'Ah, yes. Transmitters
in this are connected.'

05:33.125 --> 05:36.875
And sometimes, because of cross
connection, it makes weird noises.

05:36.916 --> 05:38.375
'Yes sir, you're right.'

05:38.666 --> 05:41.375
Sir, now that it's working,
Can I take it back?

05:42.208 --> 05:43.500
You can take this.

05:45.291 --> 05:46.750
And I'm curious to know

05:46.833 --> 05:50.333
Where and when
did your dad buy this radio?

05:50.375 --> 05:52.125
That's a long story, sir!

05:52.166 --> 05:54.125
I'll introduce him
when you come home.

05:54.166 --> 05:56.208
You can discuss this over a peg!

05:57.583 --> 06:00.125
All right.
Take it for now.

06:00.166 --> 06:01.208
- Yes, sir.
- As I said

06:01.291 --> 06:03.125
I'd like to re-examine later.

06:03.208 --> 06:05.583
Sure, sir. Bye.
Thank you so much!

06:05.875 --> 06:07.125
Welcome, bye

06:49.708 --> 06:50.750
Danny, call!

07:01.875 --> 07:03.041
I'll be back.

07:04.166 --> 07:05.291
'Papa!'

07:05.333 --> 07:07.250
Where are you?

07:07.375 --> 07:09.125
Papa, I'm still out.

07:09.250 --> 07:10.583
I'll be late.

07:10.791 --> 07:12.333
It's raining heavily.

07:12.375 --> 07:14.208
Please convince him, dad.

07:14.291 --> 07:16.875
You always have some
excuse up your sleeve!

07:17.791 --> 07:20.375
- The kids have been waiting to cut the cake.
- I know, papa.

07:20.416 --> 07:22.833
He's been asking
'When will papa come'

07:22.875 --> 07:25.250
Sorry, papa. I'll be back soon.

07:25.291 --> 07:27.666
- Okay, be safe.
- Bye.

08:18.083 --> 08:20.666
Stop...help

08:36.375 --> 08:38.500
'The mind is a little obscure'

08:39.791 --> 08:41.583
'Everything is Perspicuous'

08:42.458 --> 08:44.166
'Holding on to your finger'

08:44.791 --> 08:46.458
'The sough of your compassion'

08:47.166 --> 08:49.375
'The strength I gain when you are beside'

08:49.791 --> 08:51.875
'The day I called you father'

08:52.625 --> 08:54.166
'Everything is Perspicuous'

08:55.291 --> 08:57.125
'Except for your reflection'

08:57.708 --> 08:59.541
'The spark in your eyes'

08:59.875 --> 09:01.583
'The sonorous voice'

09:01.916 --> 09:03.791
'A joy to be around you'

09:04.208 --> 09:05.875
'I Reminisce everything'

09:07.750 --> 09:09.208
'Apart from your latent image'

09:10.166 --> 09:11.833
'If time can lapse back'

09:12.416 --> 09:14.333
'And rewrite the fate'

09:15.000 --> 09:17.708
'How joyous it is to meet you again!'

09:18.625 --> 09:20.583
'No...'

09:21.875 --> 09:23.833
'My covet makes no sense'

09:24.458 --> 09:27.208
'Our story has no conclusion'

09:27.958 --> 09:29.458
'but just prelude'

09:29.958 --> 09:32.833
'The mind is a little obscure'

09:33.458 --> 09:36.333
'The mind is a little obscure'

09:36.416 --> 09:38.625
'Murphy'

10:04.000 --> 10:05.916
"Our family"

10:06.000 --> 10:07.875
"Our rules"

10:08.041 --> 10:12.000
"In this tiny little home"

10:12.083 --> 10:14.000
"Our happiness"

10:14.041 --> 10:16.000
"Our sadness"

10:16.041 --> 10:19.875
"Everything is here, within the walls"

10:19.916 --> 10:21.833
"A beautiful girl from the home town"

10:21.875 --> 10:23.875
"Enticed me"

10:23.916 --> 10:28.000
"Now we have our children
filled in our home"

10:28.041 --> 10:31.875
"And I am going crazy"

10:32.000 --> 10:35.375
"but I still want one more"

10:35.875 --> 10:38.041
"Our family"

10:38.083 --> 10:39.916
"Our rules"

10:39.958 --> 10:44.041
"In this tiny little home"

10:44.083 --> 10:45.875
"Our happiness"

10:45.958 --> 10:47.916
"Our sadness"

10:47.958 --> 10:51.625
"Everything is here, within the walls"

11:00.375 --> 11:01.791
(Radio song stops)

11:12.083 --> 11:20.083
(Radio Starts Playing Again)

11:20.541 --> 11:22.708
(Radio Song Stops)

11:29.250 --> 11:31.458
How do you pretend like
nothing's happened, Richie?

11:32.208 --> 11:34.333
For the past 20 years
I've seen it malfunction

11:34.416 --> 11:36.458
Did you ever let me touch it, even once?

11:39.208 --> 11:40.916
Now if I want to repair it,

11:41.583 --> 11:42.958
what's your problem?

11:44.000 --> 11:45.708
I'm an electrical student.

11:46.500 --> 11:47.791
But what's the use, Richie?

11:49.833 --> 11:53.166
Richie, I'm talking to you.

11:54.000 --> 11:55.125
Please respond!

11:57.375 --> 11:58.583
I can hear you.

11:59.708 --> 12:01.041
You're right.

12:01.916 --> 12:03.291
But...

12:04.166 --> 12:05.625
I'll tell you something.

12:06.791 --> 12:09.708
What he needs is
not your electrical degree.

12:10.500 --> 12:11.666
It's love.

12:12.083 --> 12:14.291
And I am here to give him that love

12:15.541 --> 12:17.333
So don't worry about it.

12:17.791 --> 12:19.500
It's better if you
mind your own business.

12:20.750 --> 12:21.750
Correct, Richie.

12:22.500 --> 12:23.875
Why should I worry about it?

12:24.875 --> 12:26.166
To you, he's a son.

12:27.291 --> 12:28.958
But is not a father to me, isn't it?

12:36.333 --> 12:37.916
And you know what, Richie...

12:39.375 --> 12:40.666
I miss him too...

12:41.750 --> 12:43.166
I miss him too...

13:18.666 --> 13:19.833
David!

13:19.875 --> 13:22.833
How many times have I told
you not to enter this room!

13:22.916 --> 13:24.125
Why did you come here?

13:26.833 --> 13:28.500
Why are you
still standing here?

13:28.541 --> 13:29.666
Get lost!

13:33.083 --> 13:34.333
Go out!

14:31.875 --> 14:32.958
David

14:35.208 --> 14:36.250
'David!'

15:11.541 --> 15:12.583
David!

15:13.500 --> 15:16.875
You hug me despite slapping you.
How shameless of you!

15:18.375 --> 15:20.041
Go say that to someone
who has some shame.

15:20.083 --> 15:21.708
If you get to know
what I've got

15:21.791 --> 15:23.541
you will forget
that you slapped me.

15:25.250 --> 15:26.458
What's that?

15:28.666 --> 15:30.000
Radio manual.

15:30.250 --> 15:33.375
The amount of challenges
I faced to find this for you!

15:34.125 --> 15:36.541
Even if a child reads this,
it will understand the content,

15:36.583 --> 15:39.916
and assemble the radio
as easy as a toy!

15:39.958 --> 15:43.666
he's put every detail in it
with figures, Mr. Lays Charles!

15:44.416 --> 15:46.833
It's not Lays or Kurkure.
Louis Charles.

15:46.875 --> 15:48.666
Consider it a print
mistake while talking.

15:48.708 --> 15:50.083
Kindly adjust.

15:50.125 --> 15:51.291
It won't work out Alex.

15:51.333 --> 15:53.791
For 20 years, Richie hasn't even
let you touch that radio.

15:53.833 --> 15:56.458
So you're worried how
he'll allow you to repair it now.

15:56.500 --> 15:57.791
I have a plan for it.

15:57.833 --> 15:59.625
Tell me Richie's daily routine.

16:00.333 --> 16:01.875
Why? Don't you know?

16:03.625 --> 16:05.083
I want to hear it from you.

16:06.500 --> 16:07.833
What else routine will he have?

16:07.875 --> 16:10.083
At 10 am, he leaves the house.

16:10.125 --> 16:11.958
At 10:30 am, he's at Tony uncle's cafe.

16:12.000 --> 16:15.500
He leaves the cafe at 4:30 pm
and comes home at 5 pm.

16:15.625 --> 16:18.458
What if he comes
before 5 pm tomorrow?

16:19.375 --> 16:20.416
Good question.

16:21.041 --> 16:22.708
In case, Richie comes early

16:22.750 --> 16:24.541
I have an idea to avoid him.

16:24.708 --> 16:26.541
I shall park my bike
near your house.

16:26.666 --> 16:29.625
Richie has to pass your
home on the way to ours.

16:29.666 --> 16:31.833
When he spots my bike there,

16:31.875 --> 16:34.625
he will assume I'm in your
house and come there.

16:34.666 --> 16:35.875
As per the plan.

16:36.000 --> 16:38.375
The moment he comes there,
you give me information.

16:38.458 --> 16:40.958
And until I tell you,
keep Richie there.

16:41.208 --> 16:42.250
Okay?

16:42.375 --> 16:44.500
Rest will work wonders. Trust me.

16:44.583 --> 16:46.083
Okay. Done!

17:37.458 --> 17:38.500
Hello!

17:38.583 --> 17:40.708
Once you're old, that's it, my dear

17:40.875 --> 17:42.791
There won't be any pick up!

17:45.166 --> 17:46.333
Cheers!

17:47.375 --> 17:48.583
It's a joke, man

17:57.083 --> 17:58.416
Will it rain?

17:59.333 --> 18:02.375
Looks like it, Richie.

18:02.666 --> 18:05.250
- Hand me the umbrella.
- Messi, give it.

18:09.208 --> 18:12.541
- I better go before it rains.
- Yes, see you.

18:48.250 --> 18:49.625
(Doorbell)

18:53.458 --> 18:54.833
(Doorbell)

18:58.666 --> 18:59.708
Jessie...

19:01.083 --> 19:02.666
What are you doing here?

19:08.416 --> 19:10.541
I'm here to see Richie.
Is he there?

19:12.416 --> 19:13.583
No.

19:14.250 --> 19:17.666
I'm coming after so long,
and he's asking why I'm here. Karma.

19:19.541 --> 19:22.666
After all these days she had
to come today itself. My karma!

19:24.583 --> 19:26.000
David's bike.

19:28.291 --> 19:29.375
Okay

19:36.583 --> 19:40.291
Even if my planning goes wrong, I knew
Richie's timing won't be missed for sure.

19:40.333 --> 19:43.041
Sorry, David...mission abortion

19:49.125 --> 19:51.458
- Jessie! One moment.
- Hey, give it here

19:54.166 --> 19:56.875
'Dear Mr Murphy, congratulations.
Your plan is working out.'

19:56.916 --> 19:59.541
'As you predicted, Richie has come
to my house in search of you.'

19:59.583 --> 20:01.166
'Currently, he's batting.'

20:01.208 --> 20:04.000
'Please finish your antics fast,
or else it will be game over for you!'

20:05.750 --> 20:07.125
Richie is coming home.

20:07.166 --> 20:10.958
Jessie, the radio has to be
repaired at any cost today.

20:11.166 --> 20:14.250
Please, I'll explain later.
It might rain any moment.

20:14.291 --> 20:16.625
- David!
- You leave now, please!

20:16.666 --> 20:18.250
I just got here.
I'm not going anywhere.

20:18.291 --> 20:20.166
Jessie, please!

20:20.208 --> 20:21.750
No!

20:21.916 --> 20:23.166
Please!

20:24.291 --> 20:26.666
The umbrella is by the door.
Take it!

20:38.166 --> 20:40.208
Richie, where are you off to?
Let's watch the match.

20:40.250 --> 20:41.416
I'm not interested, man.

20:41.458 --> 20:43.166
Richie, the match...

20:44.916 --> 20:48.250
Richie, that umbrella looks like
the one you have at home.

20:48.375 --> 20:52.166
There must be 1000 such in the village.
Are they all from my home?

20:52.208 --> 20:55.666
No, Richie. Look, it is
definitely from your home.

20:58.000 --> 20:59.791
- Jessie!
- And who's holding that umbrella?

20:59.833 --> 21:01.041
That's not from your home!

21:02.291 --> 21:03.708
Is that our Jessie?

21:04.000 --> 21:05.250
Jessie!

21:06.166 --> 21:07.208
Richie

21:07.333 --> 21:09.625
There maybe many lookalikes
of our Jessie in this village!

21:09.666 --> 21:11.291
Can all Jessies be our Jessie?

21:11.333 --> 21:12.666
Ok, let it go.

21:12.750 --> 21:15.458
David's bike is here.
Where's he? At home?

21:15.708 --> 21:17.375
'This oldie asks such tough questions!'

21:17.541 --> 21:19.250
David's bike is here.

21:19.666 --> 21:21.125
Where's he? At home?

21:21.166 --> 21:22.791
I'm asking you the same!

21:22.833 --> 21:23.958
'What shall I say?'

21:24.000 --> 21:26.541
Yes. No way! No!

21:26.583 --> 21:29.291
- Either say yes. Or no.
- Jessie is home.

21:29.333 --> 21:31.041
- Don't say both!
- David isn't home.

21:31.083 --> 21:34.333
- Richie! I'll get the umbrella back for you
- Get lost!

22:54.791 --> 22:56.166
Hey, is it ready?

23:01.833 --> 23:02.916
'David.'

23:02.958 --> 23:04.333
'Tell me correctly.'

23:04.708 --> 23:07.458
Was he in the army or the CID?

23:12.958 --> 23:15.875
"Richie the tiger"

23:18.541 --> 23:21.541
"Richie the hunter"

23:24.083 --> 23:26.458
"Richie the tiger"

23:29.625 --> 23:32.666
"Richie the hunter"

23:34.166 --> 23:35.625
Hmmm...

23:39.625 --> 23:40.833
So...

23:42.541 --> 23:44.333
She had come here.

23:47.708 --> 23:48.833
Who, Richie?

23:49.416 --> 23:50.625
I know.

23:54.541 --> 23:56.666
I know you won't tell me anyway.

23:56.916 --> 24:00.583
Richie, I really don't know
who or what you're talking about.

24:00.958 --> 24:04.250
I was working in the garden
when it started to rain.

24:04.291 --> 24:08.041
And then the doorbell rang and
you both were standing there.

24:08.250 --> 24:09.416
What happened?

24:11.208 --> 24:12.875
Let me tell you something.

24:13.375 --> 24:15.541
We live in a very small town.

24:16.416 --> 24:18.375
Everyone knows everyone here.

24:19.250 --> 24:22.000
Should something go wrong,

24:23.000 --> 24:24.791
will you take responsibility for it?

24:25.958 --> 24:28.458
'Can we live with
dignity after that?'

24:28.666 --> 24:29.833
Forget about us.

24:29.875 --> 24:32.708
Have you ever thought
of that girl's future?

24:34.333 --> 24:35.958
Richie, what nonsense
are you talking?

24:36.000 --> 24:37.208
You think we're small kids?

24:37.250 --> 24:39.791
Or do you think
we're irresponsible?

24:39.958 --> 24:41.416
Richie, we're all grownups!

24:41.916 --> 24:44.041
And we very well
know what we're doing!

24:46.333 --> 24:48.000
You're all grownups now.

24:49.458 --> 24:53.500
If that girl's father gets
to know she had come here...

24:53.541 --> 24:55.916
If he does, it's fine, Richie.

24:56.458 --> 24:58.666
So what? I'll handle it.

24:58.791 --> 24:59.958
I'll do something.

25:00.000 --> 25:02.000
I don't see any problem here!

25:03.041 --> 25:06.500
So, she did come here!

25:09.125 --> 25:10.166
And you?

25:10.791 --> 25:12.458
'Were you waiting on them?'

25:13.333 --> 25:14.875
Are you a security guard for them!

25:14.916 --> 25:16.000
Idiot!

25:17.166 --> 25:19.208
Security guard? Me?

25:19.333 --> 25:21.541
It's useless talking to you.

25:23.083 --> 25:26.166
I know how to take
control of the situation.

25:27.125 --> 25:29.666
I shall go meet her tomorrow.

25:29.791 --> 25:32.625
Give me the duplicate
key of the house.

25:33.083 --> 25:39.666
From tomorrow, I will drop
and pick you up from college.

25:39.750 --> 25:41.083
Enough, Richie!

25:41.750 --> 25:43.000
What did you just say?

25:43.083 --> 25:44.250
You'll control everything?

25:44.291 --> 25:45.958
What do you take us for?

25:46.166 --> 25:48.250
You think I'm a radio
which you can control?

25:48.708 --> 25:50.375
He'll drop me and
pick me up it seems!

25:50.458 --> 25:54.583
I'm not a child to do that!
Nor are you my father!

25:54.875 --> 25:56.375
- You're not my father!
- 'David!'

25:56.416 --> 25:58.416
And, in fact you
can never be one!

25:59.291 --> 26:00.291
Shucks!

26:00.333 --> 26:01.458
David!

26:31.208 --> 26:32.333
Richie...

26:39.208 --> 26:40.291
Hi, David!

26:41.375 --> 26:42.708
My boy.

26:43.416 --> 26:44.625
Alex!

26:50.333 --> 26:51.583
Hi, Jessie.

26:56.708 --> 26:58.041
Sorry...

27:01.708 --> 27:03.041
What happened, David?

27:05.083 --> 27:06.291
What's the matter, dude?

27:06.333 --> 27:07.583
Just tell me!

27:07.625 --> 27:09.750
What do you call
someone who unites lovers?

27:11.958 --> 27:13.416
They call him messenger of God.

27:13.500 --> 27:15.125
Isn't it?

27:16.125 --> 27:18.708
You know what Richie
called me for uniting them?

27:18.750 --> 27:20.000
What did he say?

27:21.583 --> 27:22.875
Security guard it seems.

27:22.958 --> 27:24.708
He called me a security guard!

27:25.125 --> 27:26.708
You united them both?

27:26.750 --> 27:28.333
Yes, exactly.

27:33.500 --> 27:34.958
You are a security guard, dude!

27:35.166 --> 27:37.083
For sure a security guard!

27:38.666 --> 27:41.333
- Hey, stop it you both.
- David.

27:41.541 --> 27:42.916
Why are you so worried?

27:43.833 --> 27:45.833
You know Richie, right?

27:45.875 --> 27:48.666
You can't change
what has happened. Drop it!

27:49.250 --> 27:50.291
No, Jessie.

27:50.375 --> 27:52.291
Somehow we managed it so far.

27:52.875 --> 27:54.375
Now it's destroyed!

27:55.166 --> 27:57.958
David, look here.
Listen to me.

27:58.166 --> 28:01.250
In fact, you did all of this
to give it as a gift to Richie, right?

28:02.166 --> 28:04.708
But now, don't feel
bad about it, David.

28:05.458 --> 28:09.583
Before he discovers
that the radio is conked,

28:09.625 --> 28:11.916
it's better you apologise
and tell him the truth.

28:12.416 --> 28:14.166
'Maximum, what can happen?'

28:14.208 --> 28:16.458
He might get angry and
not talk for a few days.

28:16.833 --> 28:18.541
I'm sure he'll forgive you.

28:18.791 --> 28:23.041
Besides, there's no shame
in asking Richie for forgiveness.

28:25.000 --> 28:28.416
'The heart needs to mend quickly'

28:29.375 --> 28:31.250
'We are the blind horses'

28:31.666 --> 28:33.708
'While only memories ride our back'

28:34.583 --> 28:36.291
'Neither we are stepping back'

28:36.333 --> 28:37.916
'Nor are we lamenting'

28:38.583 --> 28:41.041
'We are just running breathlessly'

28:42.000 --> 28:43.750
'Clinging on to the bygones,'

28:43.875 --> 28:45.791
'we have forgotten
those who are here for us.'

28:46.708 --> 28:48.375
'to talk a little'

28:48.583 --> 28:50.291
'Need to equip'

28:51.833 --> 28:55.291
'The heart needs to mend quickly'

28:56.541 --> 28:58.500
'We are the blind horses'

28:59.125 --> 29:03.875
'While only memories ride our back'

29:24.791 --> 29:25.833
Richie...

31:24.041 --> 31:25.041
Richie...

31:27.416 --> 31:28.625
Richie...

32:19.166 --> 32:20.250
Shucks!

32:21.000 --> 32:22.041
Dammit!

32:33.541 --> 32:35.958
'Alex you fool! Bloody fool!'

32:39.208 --> 32:40.500
Richie will kill me

32:40.541 --> 32:42.708
'Hey! Is he crazy?'

32:42.750 --> 32:44.958
'He's switched it on and
is screaming like a mad man!'

32:45.000 --> 32:46.500
'You and your radio!'

32:46.541 --> 32:48.125
'We're getting late for practicals.'

32:48.166 --> 32:50.000
'It's the last day to submit our project.'

32:50.041 --> 32:53.583
'And today is physics practicals.
Your favourite!'

32:53.750 --> 32:54.958
'Hey, but it's not him today.'

32:55.000 --> 32:59.250
'- It's Lawrence sir today.
- If he doesn't come, will you bunk?'

32:59.291 --> 33:02.958
'Do I have to get dressed to see Lawrence?
I'm sorry. You guys go.'

33:03.000 --> 33:04.625
'Okay! Bye.'

33:05.916 --> 33:08.208
Can you hear me?

33:10.916 --> 33:12.000
Hello?

33:13.250 --> 33:14.583
'Who are you?'

33:15.083 --> 33:16.166
Hello?

33:16.416 --> 33:18.375
'I...I'm Janani.'

33:18.583 --> 33:20.583
'So did you hear
everything I said?'

33:21.125 --> 33:23.083
'Must have been a cross connection.'

33:24.416 --> 33:25.666
'Strange, isn't it?'

33:26.416 --> 33:27.500
'Who are you?'

33:27.541 --> 33:29.375
'- What's your name?
- Nanda? (mine?)

33:29.875 --> 33:31.750
Mr Nanda.

33:31.875 --> 33:34.791
- Sorry, I kept blabbering.
- No!

33:35.166 --> 33:36.875
My name is David.

33:37.000 --> 33:38.625
'Ho...Ok.'

33:38.666 --> 33:41.541
Actually, it is quite strange.

33:42.125 --> 33:46.333
'These cross connections happen
only with devices in one's area'

33:46.375 --> 33:49.541
By an chance,
are you from my area?

33:49.625 --> 33:51.833
'Your area? Which one?'

33:52.666 --> 33:53.833
Aldona.

33:54.041 --> 33:56.500
'Hey! I live in Aldona!'

33:59.000 --> 34:01.166
Really? No wonder!

34:01.500 --> 34:03.291
That's why the cross connection!

34:04.208 --> 34:06.791
In a strange way,
to get connected.

34:07.083 --> 34:08.500
Anyway

34:08.583 --> 34:10.041
By the way, what do you do?

34:10.291 --> 34:12.791
'I'm doing my Bachelors at Aloysius.'

34:15.166 --> 34:16.208
Wow!

34:16.500 --> 34:17.750
Which department?

34:17.791 --> 34:19.500
'PCM, 2ND YEAR.'

34:20.583 --> 34:23.041
Ok, I don't know what to say...

34:23.208 --> 34:24.416
You know what?

34:24.458 --> 34:25.750
I'm your senior.

34:26.041 --> 34:28.625
I'm in third year Electricals.

34:29.458 --> 34:31.833
So your name is Janani, right?

34:32.291 --> 34:34.166
Can you tell me your full name?

34:34.208 --> 34:35.791
'Janani Chandrashekhar'

34:38.708 --> 34:40.500
Miss Janani Chandrashekhar

34:40.750 --> 34:43.000
Are you sure you're from PCM?

34:43.041 --> 34:46.291
Because, I have some friends in PCM.

34:46.333 --> 34:49.083
But I've never heard
them mention you.

34:49.125 --> 34:50.416
'Really?'

34:50.791 --> 34:52.458
'Even I've never heard of you.'

34:52.583 --> 34:54.458
'Are you sure you're
from this college?'

34:54.791 --> 34:57.166
I think there's a lot of confusion.

34:57.708 --> 34:59.125
Can we catch up?

34:59.875 --> 35:01.333
Can I get your number?

35:01.708 --> 35:05.666
'I knew it the moment you asked,
'where are you from,'

35:05.708 --> 35:09.958
'which department, let's meet and
now finally phone number.'

35:10.000 --> 35:11.458
'What next? Love?'

35:11.500 --> 35:14.541
'- The moment it's a girl...'
- Hello, I have a girlfriend.

35:14.791 --> 35:16.833
She's very beautiful
and I'm sorted.

35:17.583 --> 35:20.041
I'm not looking to
make friends with you,

35:20.083 --> 35:22.083
or falling in love.

35:22.125 --> 35:23.958
Not interested!

35:24.000 --> 35:27.000
It's a cross connection, yes.
And we are in the same college.

35:27.041 --> 35:31.000
So, I want to see your
radio at least once, please!

35:31.083 --> 35:32.333
If you don't mind.

35:32.541 --> 35:36.291
'Okay. At the college sitout.
Sharp 11 am.'

35:36.416 --> 35:38.083
Done! Thank you.

35:38.791 --> 35:40.875
But how do I identify you?

35:41.333 --> 35:42.333
'Bye!'

35:45.875 --> 35:48.208
Miss Janani Chandrashekhar...

35:49.500 --> 35:50.500
Hello?

35:51.666 --> 35:52.666
Hello!

36:03.833 --> 36:04.916
David!

36:06.958 --> 36:08.000
Je...Jessie!

36:08.291 --> 36:09.791
Why did you come here?

36:10.208 --> 36:13.583
Who else can come into
your life, except for me?

36:14.208 --> 36:15.333
And by the way,

36:15.375 --> 36:18.541
- Isn't your practicals next week?
- Jessie, I was waiting for a girl.

36:18.625 --> 36:20.708
So that's why I was waiting here.

36:22.875 --> 36:24.458
So there's already someone?

36:25.041 --> 36:26.166
Not bad, David!

36:26.958 --> 36:30.166
I just merely teased
you about another girl...

36:30.833 --> 36:32.416
Wow! This is news to me.

36:32.458 --> 36:33.666
- Jessie!
- Good!

36:33.708 --> 36:34.750
What am I trying to say...

36:34.791 --> 36:36.375
and what you are saying,
I have no clue.

36:36.416 --> 36:39.041
What am I talking? Me?

36:39.500 --> 36:41.625
Okay sir, what's madam's name?

36:41.791 --> 36:44.000
- Jessie!
- What's her name?

36:45.000 --> 36:46.458
Jessie, what...

36:48.833 --> 36:50.291
Her name is Janani. But Jessie...

36:50.333 --> 36:51.416
Enough!

36:53.000 --> 36:54.000
I got it.

36:54.041 --> 36:55.375
Leave me!

36:55.791 --> 36:56.958
Janani, listen.

36:58.541 --> 36:59.958
Janani?

37:00.000 --> 37:02.875
- Jessie, let me explain.
- Janani? No, David.

37:02.958 --> 37:03.958
You know what?

37:07.208 --> 37:09.333
Janani. Jessie.

37:09.750 --> 37:11.958
Ah! Women!

38:02.250 --> 38:03.833
'Oh, Mr David!'

38:04.000 --> 38:05.125
'Are you here?'

38:05.250 --> 38:10.166
- I am! Don't you have any humanity?
'- Absolutely no humanity!'

38:10.208 --> 38:11.750
Just because
I respect you as a girl...

38:11.791 --> 38:14.458
You make a girl wait and play a joke!

38:14.541 --> 38:15.958
What kind of
a person are you, man?

38:16.000 --> 38:18.333
'What kind of a person
are you, Mr David!'

38:19.500 --> 38:22.208
Done? You're repeating
everything I want to say!

38:22.250 --> 38:24.875
- I've been waiting since 11 am!
'- Since 11 am,'

38:24.916 --> 38:28.041
'I've been roaming around
like a fool with this radio!'

38:28.083 --> 38:29.750
Exactly! That's my question.

38:29.875 --> 38:31.666
Actually, I'm angry for two reasons.

38:31.708 --> 38:33.208
One, for making you wait like a fool.

38:33.250 --> 38:35.958
- The other is, all your dialogues were mine!
- Yeah, whatever!

38:36.000 --> 38:37.958
Including the word "humanity."

38:38.625 --> 38:40.458
Janani, tell me correctly.

38:40.541 --> 38:42.625
- Are you really from my college or...
- No!

38:42.750 --> 38:45.791
'Definitely not! You are
not from my college!'

38:45.875 --> 38:48.125
'Because I'm studying
in St Aloysius college.'

38:48.166 --> 38:49.791
'Such a bloody liar!'

38:50.833 --> 38:51.833
I'm lying?

38:51.875 --> 38:53.583
I've been waiting since morning!
And you know what?

38:53.625 --> 38:54.791
I almost broke up with Jessie.

38:54.833 --> 38:56.791
- 'You're the bloody reason!'
- Jessie?

38:56.833 --> 38:58.000
A girlfriend, too?

38:58.041 --> 39:02.375
'You're the only one with a girlfriend.
We're all monks. We too have commitments.'

39:02.500 --> 39:05.541
'I couldn't even go to my department.
I had to meet my lecturer...'

39:05.583 --> 39:07.291
There's no need for this discussion.

39:07.375 --> 39:10.125
Just send me a picture
on Whatsapp. I'll identify it.

39:10.208 --> 39:12.041
'- Huh? What is that?'
- Whatsapp.

39:12.125 --> 39:13.875
On Whatsapp...ok, forget it.

39:13.916 --> 39:16.083
What's your ID on Instagram?
Tell me your Insta ID.

39:16.125 --> 39:17.250
'Whatsapp?'

39:17.500 --> 39:18.708
'What is that?'

39:18.833 --> 39:21.000
'Do you even know
what you're saying?'

39:21.083 --> 39:22.791
God knows what time
& age you're living in!

39:24.250 --> 39:26.458
Whatsapp. Instagram.

39:27.000 --> 39:28.833
You don't even have Whatsapp?

39:29.083 --> 39:32.041
Do one thing. Just ask the person
next to you to install it on your phone.

39:32.333 --> 39:33.375
'Sir'

39:33.458 --> 39:36.250
'I don't want any installment or loans.'

39:36.416 --> 39:39.333
'It's goodbye to you and the radio!'

39:39.500 --> 39:40.583
'Just leave me alone.'

39:40.625 --> 39:41.666
You don't have a phone?

39:41.708 --> 39:45.166
'Yes, the hostel number.
Only the warden uses it.'

39:45.250 --> 39:47.208
I'll give it to you. Have fun!'

39:47.250 --> 39:50.375
Oh god! Feels like I'm talking
to someone in the 90s!

39:50.416 --> 39:54.333
'In the 90s, obviously we'll talk
like it's the 90S. Not the Stone Age!'

39:55.250 --> 39:57.500
Yeah right! And you
want me to believe this!

39:57.541 --> 39:59.625
'Your belief doesn't matter to me!'

39:59.833 --> 40:02.416
'I've been tolerating you for long.
You speak nonsense!'

40:02.458 --> 40:04.833
Are you aware of
what you're saying?

40:05.083 --> 40:09.041
Or have you had a head injury and
woken up from a coma after 25 years?

40:09.083 --> 40:10.750
Ask somebody who is next to you!

40:10.791 --> 40:13.833
'Enough David. I have
heard enough of you.'

40:14.083 --> 40:16.875
'I want to watch the World Cup match.
I have to go. Bye.'

40:17.166 --> 40:19.125
Wait! World Cup?

40:19.291 --> 40:20.875
Betting on the highlights itself!

40:21.333 --> 40:22.666
Super, I appreciate it

40:22.750 --> 40:26.416
'David, stop bullshitting.
You're seriously irritating me!'

40:26.458 --> 40:27.958
'There's a limit to joking.'

40:28.000 --> 40:31.166
'Talking to you, I've
missed half the innings!'

40:31.208 --> 40:32.625
'Please let me go!'

40:32.708 --> 40:34.708
The team has already
won and is back home.

40:34.791 --> 40:36.583
What will you do watching
the highlights now?

40:36.625 --> 40:40.833
Hello, even I know they'll win...
But I want to see my Sachin making us win.

40:41.000 --> 40:42.041
Tendulkar?

40:47.333 --> 40:49.458
He retired in 2013!

40:49.541 --> 40:52.291
Why will he come now and
win the World Cup for you?

40:55.041 --> 40:56.250
Do one thing,

40:56.333 --> 40:58.958
I think you need to
get mentally checked!

41:08.333 --> 41:09.875
- Janani...
- How could you?

41:10.416 --> 41:11.708
Are you crying?

41:11.833 --> 41:13.041
'How could you?'

41:14.375 --> 41:16.333
Okay, listen.

41:16.791 --> 41:17.875
I'm sorry.

41:18.166 --> 41:21.750
'You're making
fun of me, it's okay.'

41:22.875 --> 41:24.541
'But my Sacchu?'

41:24.791 --> 41:26.083
Sacchu?

41:26.500 --> 41:27.750
'Enough.'

41:28.291 --> 41:31.041
'- I can't bear this pain.'
- Janani, listen.

41:31.208 --> 41:33.083
I'm so sorry! Correct.

41:33.875 --> 41:35.250
Whatever you're saying is correct.

41:35.291 --> 41:36.791
Actually, I'm unable to understand.

41:37.708 --> 41:38.791
Okay.

41:38.833 --> 41:40.083
You're watching the match, right?

41:40.125 --> 41:42.583
At least, can you tell
me which one it is?

41:42.875 --> 41:47.125
'World Cup semi finals.
India vs Sri Lanka.'

41:49.000 --> 41:50.250
India vs Sri Lanka.

41:50.708 --> 41:52.000
Highlights, right?

41:52.250 --> 41:55.500
13th March 1996 and it is live!

41:57.500 --> 41:59.041
- Live?
- 'Yes'

41:59.125 --> 42:01.041
'And thanks for making me cry!'

42:01.708 --> 42:02.750
Look

42:02.916 --> 42:04.000
I'm sorry.

42:04.250 --> 42:07.583
Janani, I'm finding it so
hard to believe this...

42:07.666 --> 42:09.625
As much as you being in 1996 is true,

42:09.708 --> 42:11.750
me being in 2024 is just as true.

42:11.791 --> 42:13.291
And I can prove that to you.

42:13.583 --> 42:15.208
'Oh! New story!'

42:15.458 --> 42:17.291
'Let's get it aired
on Surabhi (90s TV programme)'

42:17.333 --> 42:20.291
'For your kind information,
it was not so nice to speak to you, bye'

42:20.333 --> 42:23.250
Janani! One moment, please!

42:23.583 --> 42:27.000
You can erase these 10 minutes
from your life, later. Please!

42:27.125 --> 42:28.583
One last chance, okay?

42:30.291 --> 42:31.416
Janani?

42:32.666 --> 42:33.833
'Yeah...'

42:33.875 --> 42:35.333
Okay, yeah.

42:37.208 --> 42:38.750
'How much longer?'

42:39.625 --> 42:41.291
One moment. The Net speed...

42:41.875 --> 42:44.791
'talking about internet
speed with a pager, karma'

42:46.166 --> 42:47.583
'I have to go'

42:48.416 --> 42:49.916
'David, I can't wait.'

42:52.166 --> 42:53.541
I'm extremely sorry.

42:55.125 --> 42:56.250
In the 34th over,

42:56.291 --> 42:57.583
a fight breaks out.

42:57.875 --> 42:59.041
And the audience

42:59.083 --> 43:00.458
begin to throw bottles.

43:01.791 --> 43:04.500
Keeping all the safety &
security issues in mind,

43:05.041 --> 43:06.458
based on the run rate,

43:06.750 --> 43:08.833
Sri Lanka is declared as the winner.

43:08.875 --> 43:11.166
'What? To hell with you, man!'

43:11.666 --> 43:13.458
What? To hell with me?

43:17.416 --> 43:18.541
Okay.

43:19.458 --> 43:20.708
Miss Janani

43:21.083 --> 43:23.916
Tomorrow same place, same time

43:24.500 --> 43:26.291
you will be back for sure.

43:26.333 --> 43:28.083
And agree to everything I said.

43:29.333 --> 43:30.458
Wanna take a bet?

43:30.500 --> 43:32.625
'Yeah, I'll come running.'

43:32.833 --> 43:34.041
'Keep dreaming.'

43:35.625 --> 43:36.791
I'll be waiting!

43:48.375 --> 43:51.375
'Is she lying or am I delusional?'

44:52.458 --> 44:53.875
Wow!

45:28.250 --> 45:31.000
'In the 34th over, a fight breaks out.'

45:32.541 --> 45:34.875
'The audience will begin throwing bottles.'

45:37.958 --> 45:40.708
'Keeping all safety and
security issues in mind,'

45:41.208 --> 45:42.666
'based on the run rate,'

45:42.916 --> 45:45.166
'Sri Lanka is declared as the winner.'

46:26.500 --> 46:27.583
'David...'

46:51.708 --> 46:54.291
'Richie, good morning.
Where are you? What you upto?'

46:54.333 --> 46:59.125
'I'll be anywhere I want and with whoever
I want. That is none of your business.'

46:59.166 --> 47:00.666
Richie, why are you
getting angry now?

47:00.708 --> 47:03.458
'Are you my father to ask me all this?
You're not my father.'

47:03.500 --> 47:05.708
'In fact, you can never be one.'

47:05.750 --> 47:06.875
Oh! Counter dialogue.

47:32.500 --> 47:33.625
'Janani...'

47:37.541 --> 47:39.083
David, are you there?

47:39.125 --> 47:40.166
'Yeah'

47:40.791 --> 47:42.250
Did you watch the match?

47:44.375 --> 47:45.833
Sri Lanka won, isn't it?

47:46.291 --> 47:47.833
There was a fight, too.

47:48.333 --> 47:50.333
'- Kambli was crying.'
- Yes, I told you!

47:50.750 --> 47:52.250
But, how David?

47:52.291 --> 47:53.958
Because I'm from the future.

47:55.625 --> 47:57.666
But I'm unable to believe you.

47:58.375 --> 47:59.750
I'm scared.

48:00.000 --> 48:01.833
'Janani, why should you be scared?'

48:02.291 --> 48:05.250
Something unique is
happening between us.

48:05.458 --> 48:06.833
Don't you think this is magical?

48:06.875 --> 48:09.541
Don't you think there
is a greater purpose to it?

48:09.666 --> 48:11.500
Whatever the purpose may be,

48:11.625 --> 48:13.875
I'm having a hard
time believing it.

48:14.750 --> 48:18.666
Is this even real
or a mere illusion?

48:19.708 --> 48:20.875
But how?

48:22.125 --> 48:23.125
Janani

48:23.208 --> 48:25.625
How and why it happened is
something even I don't know.

48:25.833 --> 48:27.000
But the fact is that

48:27.041 --> 48:28.375
this has happened.

48:28.541 --> 48:32.833
There's a saying that one must
never question the origins of a monk.

48:32.916 --> 48:36.250
Likewise, let's not
get into the details.

48:36.333 --> 48:38.875
'Even we don't know how long
this radio will function this way.'

48:39.875 --> 48:41.750
'So until it lasts,
let's happily talk!'

48:42.000 --> 48:43.416
The day it stops working,

48:44.583 --> 48:47.291
we will think of it as
a miracle and cherish it.

48:47.333 --> 48:49.625
'Also, there's a terror in my house.'

48:49.666 --> 48:52.250
'It's my grandpa & he should never
get to know about this radio.'

48:52.291 --> 48:53.833
'So we talk between
11 am & 4 pm, okay?'

48:53.875 --> 48:55.708
- 'Okay...'
- Okay...

48:56.875 --> 48:58.125
What next?

48:58.958 --> 49:02.375
Every day, conversations from
the past to the future will be on.

49:02.708 --> 49:04.291
I'll introduce my friends to you.

49:05.166 --> 49:07.583
And you introduce your
friends to me, that's it.

49:09.083 --> 49:10.375
David...

49:10.416 --> 49:13.875
To be honest, I don't have
friends who will believe all this.

49:14.541 --> 49:18.083
And no close friends at all.

49:19.791 --> 49:21.416
I'm actually an orphan.

49:23.083 --> 49:25.416
'Think of me as a lone soul.'

49:25.666 --> 49:26.916
That's okay!

49:26.958 --> 49:28.916
I have a very good bunch of friends

49:28.958 --> 49:30.500
I'll introduce you to them.

49:30.541 --> 49:33.541
And now on you must never
think you have no friends.

49:33.583 --> 49:35.208
That's how I'll treat you!

49:35.250 --> 49:36.541
Let's talk everyday!

49:37.041 --> 49:38.125
What say?

49:39.541 --> 49:40.625
Okay!

49:42.500 --> 49:43.791
So tell me

49:43.833 --> 49:45.333
Is Jessie your girlfriend?

49:48.125 --> 49:49.166
Yeah.

49:49.250 --> 49:51.291
Jessie is my girlfriend.

50:01.041 --> 50:04.083
"O mind, like a flower"

50:04.125 --> 50:07.125
"Journey forth"

50:08.958 --> 50:14.375
"Journey forth with joy"

50:17.000 --> 50:18.791
"O gentle breeze"

50:18.833 --> 50:20.083
"Convey the message"

50:20.125 --> 50:23.750
"convey it softly"

50:25.125 --> 50:30.541
"Journey forth with joy"

50:32.416 --> 50:35.875
"Every day a newness"

50:36.333 --> 50:39.916
"An embrace, again and again"

50:40.541 --> 50:44.291
"Why stand so far away, my dear"

50:44.333 --> 50:47.000
"when I sing?"

50:47.291 --> 50:49.000
'This poem is so beautiful!'

50:49.208 --> 50:50.541
Specially this line

50:52.125 --> 50:54.791
'Nanna Preetige
Ninna Bennu Sothiralu'

50:56.208 --> 50:57.416
